oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: World War I Victory Medal
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This World War I Victory Medal is missing its suspension ribbon. These medals were issued to all American sodliers who served in World War I. The front depcits "Victory" as a winged female warrior. The reverse has the US National shield beneath a fasces with a double headed axe. To either side is a list of the victorious allied powers. This medal belonged to one of the three Calliham brothers of Fulton, Kentucky. All three served during World War I.
